Is it?  Linux seems much more friendly to developers of proprietary software
than a GNU system would or should be.  From a philosophical point of view,
Linux is closer to Unix than to GNU--it is a Unix system that uses most of
the GNU utilities, but does not embrace the GNU philosophy.
--Tim Smith
